      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD) is a concours-level example featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powertrain delivers a linear power band with a flawless transition between the primary and secondary turbines. Its front-midship engine placement ensures a perfect 50:50 weight distribution, working in tandem with the original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential for neutral cornering dynamics. The chassis maintains its factory torsional rigidity, and the vacuum system\u2014a critical component of the FD\u2019s complex forced induction\u2014is in pristine condition. With excellent compression across all rotor faces and a sub-2,800 lb curb weight, this specimen offers a pure, analog driving experience that is increasingly rare in the modern market.",
